# Mozilla engine

Based on tensorflow. Currently only English is supported.

* [Github repository](https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech)

Corpora used for training:

* [TED LIUM](http://www-lium.univ-lemans.fr/en/content/ted-lium-corpus) Transcripts of the TED talks. License: Creative Commons BY-NC-ND 3.0 (non-commercial, no-derivatives)
* [LibriSpeech corpus](http://www.openslr.org/12/) Created for training Kaldi.
Also included are commercial Fisher and Switchboard corpora.

They also gathered some data of their own:

* [Common voice data: licensed as public domain](https://voice.mozilla.org/data) Currently English only, will support other languages in 2018.

Summary of mozilla team achievements is [here](https://hacks.mozilla.org/2017/11/a-journey-to-10-word-error-rate/) (blog post). Also contains a lot of information on the model. 

